--- SCENARIO: open draft posts pools publicly; status holds the metadata ---
# Players register from the group without opening a private chat, so the bot cannot DM them: each
# pick pool is posted publicly as a generated image. Slot order and the chosen map live in the
# status message; only the draft-start milestone pings the group (a reply that backlinks the status).

--- CHAT ---
alice: /lobby
bob: /register
carol: /register
ambotorix: <status *Status: waiting*Players (3): alice, bob, carol*>

alice: /start
ambotorix: 🎮 Draft started by @alice* <backlink>
ambotorix: <status *Status: drafting*Map: {map}*Slot order:*>
# One combined image; its caption lists every player and their pool, so the contents are assertable
ambotorix: <image *Pick pools*alice: *bob: *carol: *>
ambotorix:                        # group stream fully accounted for (one milestone + one image)

# Players who never opened a private chat receive nothing in DM
--- DM (alice) ---
ambotorix:
--- DM (bob) ---
ambotorix:
--- DM (carol) ---
ambotorix:
